      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial CFD solver with documented validation history and version-controlled case files; solver release notes reviewed for relevant bug fixes.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 used under institutional software quality plan. Version control applied to all case files, boundary condition scripts, and post-processing macros. Solver verification documentation reviewed; no open defects affecting rotating-frame hemolysis calculations identified. Achieves Gradation 2 requirements for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes published benchmark test cases relevant to rotating turbomachinery and viscous blood-analog flows.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent code verification documented through published FDA critical path benchmark results (FDA nozzle, FDA pump) confirming solver accuracy for viscous internal flows. Rotating reference frame implementation verified against analytical solutions for idealized impeller flow. Code verification at Gradation 2 confirmed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence study performed using at least three systematically refined meshes; GCI reported for primary QoI (hemolysis index).",
      "rationale": "Three-level structured-dominant mesh refinement study performed: coarse (4.2M cells), medium (11.8M cells), fine (31.4M cells) with refinement ratio r = 1.41. Grid Convergence Index for normalized hemolysis index: GCI_fine = 2.1%, GCI_medium = 6.8%, indicating approach to grid-independent solution. Richardson-extrapolated hemolysis index used as reference. Discretization error formally bounded; achieves Gradation 3, exceeding MRL 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions documented and traceable; boundary conditions in CFD model match experimental setup within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental conditions fully documented: glycerol-water blood analog (viscosity 3.5 cP at 37°C), five operating points (2.5 L/min at 2500 RPM through 7.0 L/min at 3500 RPM), inlet/outlet pressure measurements. CFD boundary conditions set to match experimental values; fluid properties assigned from published viscometry data. Test condition fidelity at Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison of CFD predictions against experimental measurements using appropriate error metrics; agreement within acceptance band for primary QoI.",
      "rationale": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against experimental measurements from Morrison et al. (2018) FDA benchmark study. Mean absolute percentage error 9.3% across all operating points; all predictions within ±15% experimental uncertainty band. Pressure-head predictions within 4.8% of H-Q curve. Output comparison at Gradation 2 confirmed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (NIH, pressure head) are directly relevant to the COU decision quantity (relative hemolysis index RH for worst-case operating condition identification).",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis and relative hemolysis index are mechanistically linked quantities; both derive from the same power-law hemolysis damage accumulation model applied to CFD-predicted shear stress and exposure time fields. Pressure head validates the underlying flow field that drives hemolysis prediction. QoI relevance to COU decision criterion (RH < 1) confirmed at Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities performed on geometry and operating conditions sufficiently representative of the COU device and use scenario.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump, which is the same geometry as the COU device. Operating conditions span the COU flow-speed envelope (2.5–7.0 L/min, 2500–3500 RPM). Blood analog fluid properties match COU blood viscosity range. Validation scenario relevance to COU at Gradation 2 confirmed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 beyond code verification already addressed under numerical code verification factor.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, separate numerical solver error assessment beyond the code verification activities already documented is not required. Solver residual convergence to 1e-6 for all equations monitored and confirmed for each simulation. This factor is not assessed as a standalone activity; code verification factor subsumes relevant concerns at this risk level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required as standalone assessment at MRL 2; addressed through software quality assurance procedures.",
      "rationale": "Use error risks mitigated through the software quality assurance activities documented under that factor, including version-controlled case files and peer review of boundary condition setup. Standalone use error assessment not required at MRL 2 and not performed as a separate credibility factor activity."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; model form uncertainty acknowledged in COU description.",
      "rationale": "Steady-state MRF (multiple reference frame) approach with k-omega SST turbulence closure and power-law hemolysis damage model selected based on published literature for centrifugal blood pumps. Model form uncertainty associated with turbulence closure and hemolysis model constants acknowledged but formal model form assessment not required at MRL 2. Validation results provide indirect evidence of adequate model form for the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
