    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou1-cpb-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/org/computational-biofluidics-lab",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation levels for MRL 2. Discretization error exceeds requirements at Gradation 3. Validation results demonstrate CFD prediction of relative hemolysis index within 15% of experimental measurements across all five COU operating points, with RH < 1 criterion satisfied. Six factors not assessed are acceptable at MRL 2 given the medium model influence and the availability of direct experimental comparisons that provide confidence in the overall model fidelity. The credibility body of evidence is sufficient to support the regulatory decision for this Class II CPB device.",
